&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;GREATER MANCHESTER MENTAL HEALTH NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Consultant in General Adult Psychiatry&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Meadowbrook Inpatient Psychiatric Unit Salford, Eagleton Ward&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;11 Programmed Activities &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Permanent&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We at the Salford Meadowbrook unit are looking for an enthusiastic General Adult inpatient psychiatry consultant colleague. We are a supportive and flexible team and have good junior doctor cover both on the wards and when on call.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Salford psychiatry is part of Greater Manchester Mental Health NHS Foundation Trust, which came into being in January 2017 and followed the acquisition of Manchester Mental Health and Social Care NHS Trust by Greater Manchester West Mental Health NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Trust provides a wide range of local services to Manchester, Bolton, Salford and Trafford residents. In addition, the Trust provides a number of specialist and secure mental health services supporting Greater Manchester, the North West and beyond. This means that we are well supported by specialist services and have multiple opportunities to develop special interests in sub specialities and research competencies.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Chief Executive of the Trust is Neil Thwaite. The Chair is Mr Rupert Nichols. The Medical Director is Dr Alice Seabourne and Dr Chris Daly is the Deputy Medical Director and Responsible Officer for the Trust. There is a Leadership development program for new consultants who join the Trust.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is a full time appointment for a consultant to work on the General Adult psychiatry inpatient unit based at Meadowbrook unit, Eagleton Ward , Salford. This is a replacement post.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Appointee will participate in the consultant on-call rota within Salford. Currently this is a 1 in 17 rota. The on-call would be pro-rata this attracts a category A payment.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please refer to the job description and the person specification for further details about the post. This is currently being approved by The Royal College. Successful candidate will be given approved JD &amp; PS.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Martin EarlJob titleLead ConsultantEmail addressmartin.earl@gmmh.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
